<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I didn't want to add a custom validators and decided to override my form's isValid() instead. Doing my custom logic there was straightforward, except that I couldn't set the errors on my elements as they are managed internally by Zend_Form_Element with no public accessors.</p>

<p>I propose that we add public accessors for errors and messages. It makes sense regardless of the use case I demonstrated.</p>

    </div>
